{"content": "Given the function:\n\n\\[\nf(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x\n\\]\n\nWe are told:\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 3\n\\]\n\nWe need to find \\( f(-5) \\).\n\nLet's calculate \\( f(5) \\) and \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 5^7 + a \\cdot 5^3 + c \\cdot 5\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a \\cdot (-5)^3 + c \\cdot (-5)\n\\]\n\nLet's compute the powers:\n\n- \\( 5^7 = 78125 \\)\n- \\( 5^3 = 125 \\)\n- \\( (-5)^7 = -78125 \\)\n- \\( (-5)^3 = -125 \\)\n\nSo,\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 78125 + 125a + 5c\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\nNow, let's add the two:\n\n\\[\nf(5) + f(-5) = (78125 + 125a + 5c) + (-78125 - 125a - 5c) = 0\n\\]\n\nSo,\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = -f(5)\n\\]\n\nGiven \\( f(5) = 3 \\):\n\n", "in": 86, "out": 300}